<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-02T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/625</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BBA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-02T10:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your May 25, 4 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs states that Haitian
                                Government has been approached regarding conference and will reply,
                                expressing regret that in view of the financial situation of the
                                Republic of Haiti it will be unable to be represented at the
                                conference.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BBA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>